Title: Pope Francis Calls on United Nations to Work for Peace, Justice; Pontiff's speech ties environmental threats with social issues
Abstract: The pope, who has said the use of armed force against Islamic State might be legitimate if exercised on a multilateral basis, echoed the Vatican's criticism of the 2003 U.S.-led invasion of Iraq--and his own opposition to U.S. airstrikes in Syria a decade later--by warning against intervention that ignores international law and the need for "negotiation, mediation and arbitration."

Title: Fear Arrives in South Carolina Long Before Any Actual Syrians
Abstract: None of Syria's four million refugees have been resettled in this part of South Carolina in the last year, according to the State Department. Since May, a Christian nonprofit group, World Relief, has placed 32 refugees in the region, but most of them were Christians fleeing troubled countries like Myanmar and the Democratic Republic of Congo. Representative Trey Gowdy, a Republican whose district is part of the Upstate region and who leads the House select committee investigating the attack on the American diplomatic compound in Benghazi, Libya, has complained that the federal government did not sufficiently coordinate with local officials before allowing the current crop of refugees to arrive.
